CatDescriptText: Mrs. Wilner Robinson, 538 Herron Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "In your opinion, what constitutes the 'Leadership' in Negro community in Pittsburgh? What do you think of that which exists?" answer reads: "We have made progress in the last seven or eight years and this is mainly because Negro leadership has dept plugging away and preaching.  Most of the progress has been because our leaders have fought for it."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Wilner Robinson wearing striped hat and dark coat, holding eyeglasses and dark handbag, standing in front of Rosenbaum Company, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
